trans-unit.source: Encapsulates the HTTP intrinsic object that provides a collection of application-scoped objects for the <xref href="System.Web.HttpApplicationState.StaticObjects"></xref> property.

The <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollectionWrapper> class derives from the <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollectionBase> class and serves as a wrapper for the <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollection> class.
This class exposes the functionality of the <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollection> class while also exposing the <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollectionBase> type.

The <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollectionBase> class enables you to replace the original implementation of the <xref:System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollection> class in your application with a custom implementation, such as when you perform unit testing outside the ASP.NET pipeline.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollectionWrapper"></xref> class.
The object that this wrapper class provides access to.
httpStaticObjectsCollection is `null`.
Copies the elements of the collection to an array, starting at the specified index in the array.
The one-dimensional array that is the destination of the elements that are copied from the collection.
The array must have zero-based indexing.
The zero-based index in array at which to begin copying.
Gets the number of objects in the collection.
The number of objects in the collection.
Returns an enumerator that can be used to iterate through the collection.
An object that can be used to iterate through the collection.
Returns the object that has the specified name from the collection.
The case-insensitive name of the object to return.
The object that is specified by name, if found; otherwise, `null`.
Gets a value that indicates whether the collection is read-only.
`true` in all cases.
Gets a value that indicates whether the collection is thread-safe.
`false` in all cases.
Gets the object that has the specified name from the collection.
The case-insensitive name of the object to get.
The object that is specified by name, if found; otherwise, `null`.
Gets a value that indicates whether the collection has been accessed.
`true` if the collection has never been accessed; otherwise, `false`.
Writes the contents of the collection to a <xref href="System.IO.BinaryWriter"></xref> object.
The object to use to write the serialized collection to a stream or encoded string.
Gets an object that can be used to synchronize access to the collection.
The current instance of the <xref href="System.Web.HttpStaticObjectsCollection"></xref> class that is wrapped by this class.
